{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "metaball", "icon": "SOP/metaball", "tags": "create, metaball", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Metaball"], "extent": [0, 13]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Creates metaballs and meta-superquadric surfaces."], "extent": [105, 162]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node creates metaballs and metasurfaces. If you\nclick and drag the mouse on the Construction Plane, it generates a\nmetaball whose X radius is specified by your drag. Metasurfaces are\ngeneralized metaballs meaning that they aren\u2019t necessarily ellipsoidal."], "extent": [162, 423]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Introduction"], "extent": [423, 442], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Metaballs provide a method for creating an organic-looking surface. The\nmetaballs are blobs (", {"type": "q", "text": ["fields"]}, ") of ", {"type": "q", "text": ["density"]}, " floating in space. Houdini\nskins a surface around areas where the density is greater than some\nthreshold."], "extent": [442, 666]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["When two metaballs overlap, Houdini adds their field effects together.\nBecause the density of the force field can be increased by the proximity\nof other metaball force fields, metaballs have the unique property that\nthey change their shape to adapt and fuse with surrounding metaballs.\nThis makes them very effective for modeling organic surfaces."], "extent": [666, 1015]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["You can specify negative Weights to create ", {"type": "q", "text": ["pusher"]}, " metaballs. This lets\nyou create holes in the surface by effectively subtracting density."], "extent": [1015, 1157]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The field is controlled by a ", {"type": "em", "text": ["kernel function"]}, " and a ", {"type": "em", "text": ["weight"]}, ". The\nkernel function controls the gradient of the density value of a metaball\nfield from 1 (at the center) to 0 (at its outside edge). The weight\nscales the density to shift the location of the surface closer or\nfurther away from the center. You can currently specify the shape of the\nfield as an ellipsoid or a ", {"type": "em", "text": ["super-quadric"]}, "."], "extent": [1157, 1549]}, {"level": 3, "id": "includeme", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Placing Metaballs"], "extent": [290, 326], "body": [{"type": "task_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": ["Place the metaball anywhere in the scene"], "role": "item", "extent": [326, 383], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "indent": 8, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SOP/metaball", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/metaball.html"}, " ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/nodes/sop/metaball", "type": "link", "text": ["Metaball"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/metaball.html"}, " tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Create"]}, " tab."], "extent": [383, 495]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "indent": 8, "text": ["Move the cursor into the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/ref/views/3dview", "type": "link", "text": ["scene view"], "fullpath": "/ref/views/3dview.html"}, ". "], "extent": [495, 563], "body": [{"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 12, "role": "item", "extent": [563, 581], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "text": ["You can hold ", {"keys": ["Alt"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " to detach the metaball from the construction plane."], "extent": [581, 683]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "indent": 8, "text": ["Click ", {"keys": ["LMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " to place the metaball anywhere in the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/ref/views/3dview", "type": "link", "text": ["scene view"], "fullpath": "/ref/views/3dview.html"}, ". "], "extent": [683, 778], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["If you press ", {"keys": ["Enter"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " without clicking, Houdini places the metaball at the origin."], "extent": [778, 883]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": ["Place the metaball at the origin"], "role": "item", "extent": [883, 927], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Press ", {"keys": ["Ctrl", "LMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " on the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SOP/metaball", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/metaball.html"}, " ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/nodes/sop/metaball", "type": "link", "text": ["Metaball"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/metaball.html"}, " tool on the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/", "type": "link", "text": ["shelf"], "fullpath": "/shelf/index.html"}, "."], "extent": [927, 1052]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If you are at the geometry level or have an object selected and you create a ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/nodes/sop/metaball", "type": "link", "text": ["metaball"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/metaball.html"}, ", it will go into the selected object. If you are at the scene level and create a metaball, the viewer and the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/ref/panes/network", "type": "link", "text": ["network editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/network.html"}, " will switch to the geometry level of the selected object. This unique feature allows you to merge multiple metaballs together automatically by creating them sequentially and close together."], "extent": [1052, 1509]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/metaball.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [1509, 1557]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 4, "text": [" "], "role": "item", "extent": [1557, 1568], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Metaballs can be moved once they are placed by either dragging them in the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/ref/views/3dview", "type": "link", "text": ["scene view"], "fullpath": "/ref/views/3dview.html"}, " or changing the values in the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/ref/panes/parms", "type": "link", "text": ["parameter editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/parms.html"}, "."], "extent": [1568, 1759]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 4, "text": ["Metaball Handles"], "extent": [1759, 1786], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["There are special handles available at the geometry level for the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SOP/metaball", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/metaball.html"}, " ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/nodes/sop/metaball", "type": "link", "text": ["Metaball"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/metaball.html"}, " object that allow you to stretch and squash it."], "extent": [1786, 1960]}, {"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Move to the geometry level by double clicking ", {"keys": ["LMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " the metaball node in the network editor or by clicking the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Jump to Operator"]}, " button on the operation controls toolbar."], "extent": [1960, 2147]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Drag the handles to squash or stretch the metaball."], "extent": [2147, 2215]}], "container": true}, {"type": "task_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": ["Stretch or squash the metaball along the x-axis"], "role": "item", "extent": [2215, 2274], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Drag the red handle."], "extent": [2274, 2316]}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": ["Stretch or squash the metaball along the y-axis"], "role": "item", "extent": [2316, 2375], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Drag the green handle. "], "extent": [2375, 2416]}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": ["Stretch or squash the metaball along the z-axis"], "role": "item", "extent": [2416, 2475], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Drag the blue handle.  "], "extent": [2475, 2512]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/metaball_red.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}, {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/metaball_green.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}, {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/metaball_blue.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [2512, 2635]}]}]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["How to"], "extent": [1586, 1599], "body": [{"type": "task_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 0, "text": ["Make metaballs interact with each other"], "role": "item", "extent": [1599, 1647], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Merge the nodes together with a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/merge", "type": "link", "text": ["Merge operator"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/merge.html"}, "."], "extent": [1647, 1717]}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 0, "text": ["Create a large number of metaballs easily"], "role": "item", "extent": [1717, 1766], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Create a single metaball and copy it onto the points of\n    another piece of geometry with the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/copy", "type": "link", "text": ["Copy\n    operator"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/copy.html"}, "."], "extent": [1766, 1901]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Copying metaballs onto the points of a ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/dopparticles/index", "type": "link", "text": ["particle system"], "fullpath": "/dopparticles/index.html"}, "\n    is a good way to achieve various volumetric visual effects."], "extent": [1901, 2047]}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 0, "text": ["Speed up the display of metaballs"], "role": "item", "extent": [2047, 2088], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["In the viewport options menu, choose ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Display \u25b8 Display Options"]}, ", or press ", {"keys": ["D"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " to bring up the Display Options window."], "extent": [2088, 2226], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/ui/viewport_menus_anno.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [2226, 2278]}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Geometry"]}, " tab and lower the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Level Of Detail"]}, "\n      setting to get faster but rougher representations of geometry\n      in the viewer, including metaballs."], "extent": [2278, 2456]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 0, "text": ["Convert metaballs to other geometry types"], "role": "item", "extent": [2456, 2505], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/convert", "type": "link", "text": ["Convert tool"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/convert.html"}, "."], "extent": [2505, 2551]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Super-quadratic field shapes"], "extent": [2551, 2586], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Instead of the regular ellipsoid field shape, you can increase or\ndecrease the XY and Z exponent parameters to create ", {"type": "q", "text": ["star-ish"]}, "\n(exponent > 1) or ", {"type": "q", "text": ["square-ish"]}, " (exponent < 1)."], "extent": [2586, 2764]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["A metaball is known as a super-quadratic if either exponent is not\nequal to one."], "extent": [2764, 2854]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["How metaballs work"], "extent": [2854, 2879], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Each metaball has a ", {"type": "q", "text": ["sphere of influence"]}, ". When you\n", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/merge", "type": "link", "text": ["merge"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/merge.html"}, " two metaballs and they extend\ninto each other\u2019s sphere of influence, they react in a way similar to\ndrops of water: the surface tension works to form a smooth bridge\nbetween them. This is useful for making organic ", {"type": "q", "text": ["blobby"]}, " shapes which\nmeld into each other."], "extent": [2879, 3214]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Metaballs can be thought of as spherical force fields whose surface is\nan implicit function defined at any point where the density of the force\nfield equals a certain threshold. Because the density of the force field\ncan be increased by the proximity of other metaball force fields,\nmetaballs have the unique property that they change their shape to adapt\nand fuse with surrounding metaballs. This makes them very effective for\nmodeling organic surfaces. For example, below we have a metaball. The\nsurface of the metaball exists whenever the density of the metaball\u2019s\nfield reaches a certain threshold:"], "extent": [3214, 3818]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/MetaballFields.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [3818, 3860]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["When two or more metaball force fields are combined, as in the\nillustration below, the resulting density of the force fields is added,\nand the surface extends to include that area where the force fields\nintersect and create density values with a value of one. For more\ninformation on Metaballs, see the ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Geometry Types"]}, " section."], "extent": [3860, 4190]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/nodes/MetaballFieldsa.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [4190, 4233]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["You can see a metaball\u2019s sphere of influence by turning on ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Display primitive hulls"]}, " in the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/basics/ui", "type": "link", "text": ["Display options toolbar"], "fullpath": "/basics/ui.html"}, "."], "extent": [4233, 4366]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node is ideal for creating organic models, liquid effects and\nother blobby surfaces."], "extent": [4366, 4458]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Tips"], "extent": [4458, 4469], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Level of detail"], "extent": [4469, 4487], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You can change the level of detail of the metaball and NURBS display\n    by adjusting the Level of Detail parameter in display options."], "extent": [4487, 4628]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Better metaball shading"], "extent": [4628, 4653], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Accurate metaball normals will be computed if the ", {"type": "em", "text": ["normal"]}, " attribute\n    exists when conversion to polygons is done. Thus, to get improved\n    shading on polygonized metaballs, it\u2019s a good idea to add the normal\n    attribute (i.e. use a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/facet", "type": "link", "text": ["Facet SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/facet.html"}, ") before converting\n    the metaballs."], "extent": [4653, 4961]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using metaballs to prune L-system copying"], "extent": [4961, 5005], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This is\n    typically done by copying metaballs to every point of the\n    deforming a polygonal/mesh input source with a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/copy", "type": "link", "text": ["Copy\n    SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/copy.html"}, ". When doing this, it is a good idea to pass\n    any deforming geometry through a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/facet", "type": "link", "text": ["Facet SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/facet.html"}, " and\n    ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Consolidate Points"]}, " to minimize the number of points you need\n    to copy to. If converting from spline surfaces, you may want to\n    refine your surfaces first to get a smooth distribution of\n    metaballs."], "extent": [5005, 5485]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If you are using metaballs to create a deforming attractor\n    for the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/particle", "type": "link", "text": ["Particle SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/particle.html"}, ", you may want to\n    use a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/group", "type": "link", "text": ["Group SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/group.html"}, " to define a bounding area,\n    and copy the metaballs only to the points included in that\n    group. This makes it much easier to control and animate the\n    attractor area."], "extent": [5485, 5830]}], "container": true}], "container": true}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Meta Expressions"], "extent": [5830, 5853], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Metaball expressions are user-specified attributes that determine how metaballs are to be merged. To use Meta Expressions, merge all your metaballs with groups. You can reference metaballs as groups or primitive numbers. Then, use an ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/attribcreate", "type": "link", "text": ["Attribute Create SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/attribcreate.html"}, " to build a string detail called ", {"type": "code", "text": ["metaExpression"]}, "."], "extent": [5853, 6184]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [6184, 6190], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The attribute must be called ", {"type": "code", "text": ["metaExpression"]}, "."], "extent": [6190, 6242]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Then, in a string field, type your expression to control how the metaballs merge together. These expressions can be built using a combination of quoted group names, unquoted primitive numbers, and the operations ", {"type": "code", "text": ["min"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["max"]}, ", and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["sum"]}, ". An example of a valid expression is"], "extent": [6242, 6516], "body": [{"lang": null, "type": "pre", "indent": 4, "text": ["\n    sum(max(\"group1\", \"group2\"), max(\"group3\", \"group4\"), 0, 1)\n    "], "extent": [6516, 6596]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["where group1, group2, group3 and group4 are the names of groups, and 0 and 1 are the primitive numbers of metaballs. The ", {"type": "code", "text": ["min"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["max"]}, ", and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["sum"]}, " operations can take an arbitrary number of arguments and support nested expressions such as ", {"type": "code", "text": ["sum(max(...), ...)"]}, ". Arguments to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["min"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["max"]}, ", or ", {"type": "code", "text": ["sum"]}, " are separated by commas. Providing a quoted group name is equivalent to simply adding each metaball primitive from that group to the current argument list. For example, if group1 contains metaballs with primitive numbers 0, 1 and 2, then the expression"], "extent": [6596, 7145]}, {"lang": null, "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nmax(\"group1\")\n"], "extent": [7145, 7167]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["is equivalent to"], "extent": [7167, 7186]}, {"lang": null, "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nmax(0, 1, 2)\n"], "extent": [7186, 7207]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Duplicate argument names are also supported by this expression. For example, if a metaball with primitive number 0 is defined, then specifying the expression ", {"type": "code", "text": ["sum(0, 0)"]}, " is equivalent to merging two distinct metaballs at the same location as metaball 0."], "extent": [7207, 7463]}, {"type": "table", "thead": [], "body": [{"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sum "], "role": "td", "extent": [7463, 7469], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/metaball1.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [7469, 7503]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": ["Max "], "role": "td", "extent": [7503, 7509], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/metaball2.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [7509, 7543]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": ["Min "], "role": "td", "extent": [7543, 7549], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/metaball3.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [7549, 7584]}]}], "divider": false}]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This expression can be set by creating a detail/string attribute with the desired expression on any geometry containing metaballs. This functionality is also partially exposed via the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SOP/metagroups", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/SOP/metagroups.html"}, {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/metagroups", "type": "link", "text": ["MetaGroups SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/metagroups.html"}, ". This SOP allows users to easily generate expressions of the form"], "extent": [7584, 7893]}, {"lang": null, "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nmax(sum(...), sum(...), ..., sum(...))\n"], "extent": [7893, 7940]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["by establishing a set of ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/metagroups", "type": "link", "text": ["Metaball groupings"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/metagroups.html"}, ". Each of these groupings consists of a list of group names, separated by spaces. For example, if two metaball groupings are defined by the SOP, one as 'group1 group2', and the other as 'group3 group4', then the SOP generates a Metaball expression equivalent to"], "extent": [7940, 8273]}, {"lang": null, "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nmax(sum(\"group1\", \"group2\"), sum(\"group3\", \"group4\"))\n"], "extent": [8273, 8335]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [8335, 8341], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You can increase the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Level of Detail"]}, " on the Viewport tab of the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/ref/windows/displayopts_3d", "type": "link", "text": ["Display Options"], "fullpath": "/ref/windows/displayopts_3d.html"}, " to increase the accuracy at the cost of viewport performance and memory consumption."], "extent": [8341, 8545]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Advanced"], "extent": [8545, 8560], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["When generating blobby primitives in RIB, the string parameters were hard-coded to an empty list.  SOHO will now search for a detail attribute named ", {"type": "code", "text": ["RiBlobby_Strings"]}, " (case sensitive).  This value of this string will be parsed using the syntax described in the Python function ", {"type": "code", "text": ["shlex.split()"]}, ".  The resulting list of strings will be output in the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["RiBlobby()"]}, " call."], "extent": [8560, 8929]}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [8929, 8941], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Mode"], "extent": [8941, 8949], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["How to interpret the parameters used to specify the metaball."], "extent": [8949, 9016]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Field Radius"], "extent": [9016, 9034], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Treat ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Radius"]}, " as a scale on the density field.  The threshold\n        surface is then a function of this ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Radius"]}, ", ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Weight"]}, " and\n        ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Kernel Function"]}, "."], "extent": [9034, 9206]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Threshold Radius"], "extent": [9206, 9228], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Treat ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Radius"]}, " as specifying the radius of the 1.0 threshold\n        surface for this isolated metaball, and compute the corresponding\n        scale on the density field given this ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Radius"]}, ", ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Weight"]}, " and\n        ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Kernel Function"]}, ".  Changing the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Weight"]}, " in this mode will\n        not change the isolated threshold surface of this metaball."], "extent": [9228, 9587]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Radius"], "extent": [9587, 9595], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["X radius of a metaball that is placed if you click on the\n    Construction Plane without dragging. If you click and drag, the\n    size of the metaball is over-ridden by the amount of drag.\n    Entering non-equal values in the xyz fields results in\n    ellipsoidal shapes."], "extent": [9622, 9899]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The X radius is defined by the distance dragged from the center,\n    while the Y and Z radii vary proportionally with the X / Y and X\n    / Z ratios in the parameter dialog."], "extent": [9899, 10078]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "radx /rady /radz"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Center"], "extent": [10078, 10086], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Center of the metaball. This value is updated whenever you click\n    (and drag) to create a metaball. A new metaball will be\n    positioned here if you type ", {"keys": ["Enter"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, "."], "extent": [10107, 10280]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "tx /ty /tz"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Rotate"], "extent": [10280, 10288], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Rotation about the center of the metaball."], "extent": [10309, 10361]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "rx /ry /rz"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Weight"], "extent": [10361, 10369], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["How much ", {"type": "q", "text": ["pull"]}, " the metaball has on surrounding metaballs,\n    causing them to merge together."], "extent": [10390, 10494]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "metaweight"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Kernel Function"], "extent": [10494, 10511], "body": [{"type": "table", "thead": [], "body": [{"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/metaball_blinn.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [10528, 10569], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 8, "text": ["Blinn "], "role": "td", "extent": [10569, 10585], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Always puts a sphere at the blob center, even if the\n            weight is less than 1.0. The fastest and most stable of\n            all the models."], "extent": [10585, 10751]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/metaball_wyvill.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [10751, 10793], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 8, "text": ["Wyvill "], "role": "td", "extent": [10793, 10810], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The Wyvill and Elendt models are very similar. Only the\n            weight distribution function is different."], "extent": [10810, 10938]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/metaball_elendt.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [10938, 10980], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 8, "text": ["Elendt "], "role": "td", "extent": [10980, 10997], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The fastest method, but the simplest approximation, so it may not be as smooth as other functions in terms of weight distribution."], "extent": [10997, 11145]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/metaball_links.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [11145, 11186], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 8, "text": ["Links "], "role": "td", "extent": [11186, 11202], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["A piecewise polynomial."], "extent": [11202, 11251]}, {"lang": null, "type": "pre", "indent": 12, "text": ["                                                                  \n                1 - 3*t*t,  t < 1/3                                                          \n                1.5 * (1 - t)^2, t < 1                                               \n            "], "extent": [11251, 11529]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/metaball_renderman.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [11529, 11579], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 8, "text": ["RenderMan "], "role": "td", "extent": [11579, 11599], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Used by Pixar\u2019s RenderMan (and possibly other RIB\n            renderers). Defined as"], "extent": [11599, 11709]}, {"lang": null, "type": "pre", "indent": 12, "text": ["\n            Density = 1 - 3*R^2 + 3*R^4 - R^6\n            "], "extent": [11709, 11787]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/metaball_hart.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [11787, 11832], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "indent": 8, "text": ["Hart "], "role": "td", "extent": [11832, 11847], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["A kernel function suggested by mathematician John Hart."], "extent": [11847, 11928]}, {"lang": null, "type": "pre", "indent": 12, "text": ["\n                1 - 6*t^5 + 15*t^4 - 10*t^3\n            "], "extent": [11928, 12004]}]}], "divider": false}]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "kernel"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["XY Exponent"], "extent": [12004, 12022], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Determines inflation/contraction in the x and y axes."], "extent": [12038, 12097]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["For metaballs, the exponent determines the inflation towards\n    ", {"type": "q", "text": ["squarishness"]}, " or contraction towards ", {"type": "q", "text": ["starishness"]}, " as described\n    below:"], "extent": [12097, 12243]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["> 1 = metaballs that appear more like a star. < 1 = metaballs that\n    appear more squarish. 1 = metaballs that appear spherical."], "extent": [12243, 12378]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "expxy"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Z Exponent"], "extent": [12378, 12390], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Determines inflation/contraction in the z axis."], "extent": [12405, 12458]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "expz"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [12458, 12467], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/bulge", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/bulge.html"}], "extent": [12467, 12487]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/magnet", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/magnet.html"}], "extent": [12487, 12509]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Metaball"], "summary": ["Creates metaballs and meta-superquadric surfaces."], "included": ["/shelf/metaball"]}